Advanced Playwright Filtering

These are Playwright-specific locator strategies that you'll use frequently in real projects.

Filter by Text
await page
.locator(".product")
.filter({ hasText: "iPhone" })
.click();

Filter by Child Element
await page
.locator(".card")
.filter({
    has: page.locator("button")
})
.click();
has()
page.locator("article", {
    has: page.locator("img")
});
hasText()
page.locator("tr", {
    hasText: "Admin"
});
first()
page.locator(".product").first()
last()
page.locator(".product").last()
nth()
page.locator(".product").nth(3)
Locator Chaining
page
.locator("table")
.locator("tbody")
.locator("tr")
.nth(2)
.locator("button")
.click();
and()
page
.getByRole("button")
.and(page.getByTitle("Save"));
or()
page
.getByRole("button", { name: "Save" })
.or(page.getByText("Submit"));
DOM Traversing

Example HTML

<div class="card">

    <h2>iPhone 16</h2>

    <button>Add to Cart</button>

</div>

Locate Add to Cart button for iPhone

page
.locator(".card")
.filter({
    hasText: "iPhone 16"
})
.getByRole("button")
.click();

This is far more robust than relying on indexes.

